Nagpur Municipal Election Results 2017 Live Updates: Counting of votes begins Nagpur Municipal Election Results 2017 Live Updates: Counting of votes begins Nagpur witnessed 53 per cent voter turnout, only a tad better than 52 per cent seen in the last elections. By: Express Web Desk | New Delhi | Updated: February 23, 2017 10:08 am Nagpur: First time voters showing their ink marked fingers after casting votes at a polling station for the Municipal Corporation election in Nagpur on Tuesday. PTI Photo(PTI2_21_2017_000174A) 
Counting of votes for Nagpur municipal corporation elections began at 10 am on Thursday. Around 53 per cent polling was registered in the election to the Nagpur Municipal Corporation on Tuesday, state election commission officials said. The elections in Nagpur are significant as the city is the home turf of chief minister Devendra Fadnavis . Â© The Indian Express Online Media Pvt Ltd Tags:
